"According to wikipedia David Weinberger is an American technologist, professional speaker, and commentator, probably best known as co-author of the Cluetrain Manifesto (originally a website, and eventually a book, which has been described as “a primer on Internet marketing”. Weinberger’s work focuses on how the Internet is changing human relationships, communication, and society. He currently serves as a fellow at the Berkman Center for Internet and Society at Harvard Law School."


